*
                 * @function
                 * @name registerCallback
                 * @param {String} name Name of the flyout to register the callback for.
                 * @param {Function} confirmCloseCallback Function to execute when the close of the flyout is requested.
                 *   Should return a promise that resolves when the flyout can be closed.
                 * @returns {Promise}
                 * @description
                 *   Registers the confirm close callback for the passed flyout name. Don't forget to deregister the
                 *   callback before you destroy the target flyout.

*

                 * @name deregisterCallback
                 * @param {String} name Name of the flyout to deregister the callback for.
                 * @description
                 *   Registers the confirm close callback for the passed flyout name. Don't forget to deregister the
                 *   callback before you destroy the target flyout.
